<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
``Procedures for Registering Computer Security Objects'', NISTIR XXXX, September 1993.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
``U.S. Government Open Systems Interconnection Profile'' (GOSIP), FIPS PUB 146&hyph;1, April 1991.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 02 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Scope:
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 This standard specifies a security label for GOSIP-complaint implementations. It includes two label specifications,
one suitable for the OSI Application Layer, and the other for the Network Layer. GOSIP will call for the use of this standard
when optional security protocols at these layers require the use of security labels.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Applicability:
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The specified Standard Security Label (SSL) applies to OSI communications systems handling U.S. Government unclassified
but sensitive data. The SSL shall be used on OSI systems required to label data as indicated in the security chapter
of GOSIP. Although this standard is intended for use on systems handling unclassified information, it could be adopted
by the appropriate authorities for use on systems handling classified information.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The SSL may be used by OSI protocols to control access, specify protective measures, and indicate handling restrictions
required by a network security policy as registered in a Computer Security Objects Register.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Complying implementations shall be capable of transmitting, receiving, and obtaining information from security
labels based on the specifications in this document.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Specifications:
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

